iehl:</b> "(candidate last) may be the guy who pulled it out tonight." (dan riehl, "(candidate last) can't catch a break," riehl world view, <a href="http://www.riehlworldview.com/">www.riehlworldview.com/</a> , posted 5/3/07) </p><p><b>john hinderaker:</b> "if you didn't already know how good (candidate last) is, you would be really impressed by his performance tonight." (john hinderaker, "liveblogging the gop debate," power line forum, <a href="http://www.plnewsforum.com">www.plnewsforum.com</a> , posted 5/3/07) </p><p><b>columnist kathleen parker:</b> "and the winner is: mitt the good, the perfect, the gosh-darned smartest of them all. he was substantive, concise, and humorous, if somewhat over-educated for those who haven't yet read the cliff notes on altered nuclear stem cells. his answer on stem-cell research showed that he has delved deeply into the issue..." (<em>national review</em> website, <a href="http://www.nationalreview.com">www.nationalreview.com</a> , accessed 5/4/07) </p><p><b>captain's quarters' ed morrissey:</b> "who won? – (candidate full) won this debate. he looked relaxed, answered clearly, showed real warmth and a sense of humor, and actually answered the questions asked of him – even the stupid ones, to which i'll return shortly." (ed morrissey, "debate analysis: (candidate last) wins," captain's quarters blog, <a href="http://www.captainsquartersblog.com/mt/archives/009874.php">www.captainsquartersblog.com/mt/archives/009874.php</a>, posted 5/3/07) </p><p><b> <em>townhall</em>'s dean barnett:</b> "(candidate full) – (candidate last) was clearly the class of the field. i know, i'm biased, blah, blah, blah. but if you saw the debate, believe your own eyes. (candidate last) has a command of the facts and an effective delivery that must be the envy of the field. as america gets to know him in forums like this (not that i'm hoping there will be other forums precisely like this hideous one – perish that thought), the country will come to understa